    "### Interaction Feature Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Interaction features capture the **combined effect of two variables**, allowing the model to learn relationships that are not visible when variables are considered independently.\n",
    "\n",
    "We construct interactions such as:\n",
    "- **Temperature × Pressure**\n",
    "- **Vibration × Power Consumption**\n",
    "- **Conversion Rate × Yield**\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Key Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Captures joint behavior**\n",
    "  Many faults are not caused by a single variable, but by the **interaction between variables**.  \n",
    "  For example:\n",
    "  - High temperature alone may be normal  \n",
    "  - High temperature *and* high pressure together may indicate risk  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Enhances non-linear modeling**\n",
    "  Interaction terms allow even simple models (e.g., linear models) to:\n",
    "  - capture non-linear relationships  \n",
    "  - approximate complex system dynamics  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Reflects physical relationships**\n",
    "  These combinations often align with real engineering principles:\n",
    "  - temperature–pressure → thermodynamic coupling  \n",
    "  - vibration–power → mechanical load/stress  \n",
    "  - conversion–yield → process efficiency  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Improves fault separability**\n",
    "  Fault conditions may form clearer patterns in interaction space than in individual variables.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Amplifies abnormal conditions**\n",
    "  When two variables simultaneously deviate, their product:\n",
    "  - magnifies the signal  \n",
    "  - makes anomalies more distinguishable  \n",
    "\n",
    "#### Example Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "- High **temp_pressure_interaction** → system operating under combined thermal and pressure stress  \n",
    "- High **vibration_power_interaction** → potential mechanical strain or inefficiency  \n",
    "- High/low **conversion_yield_interaction** → process imbalance or degradation  \n",
    "\n",
    "#### Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "Interaction features provide a **multi-dimensional view of system behavior**, enabling the model to detect complex fault patterns driven by relationships between variables rather than isolated signals."
   ]
