    "### Missing Values After Feature Engineering — Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Lag and rolling features naturally introduce **missing values (NaNs)** at the beginning of each reactor’s time series.\n",
    "\n",
    "This occurs because:\n",
    "- A **10-step lag** requires 10 previous observations  \n",
    "- A **rolling window (e.g., 10)** cannot be computed for the initial rows  \n",
    "- Standard deviation in rolling windows may also be undefined early on  \n",
    "\n",
    "#### Key Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Structured (not random) missingness**\n",
    "  The NaNs are:\n",
    "  - predictable  \n",
    "  - systematic  \n",
    "  - caused by feature engineering (not data quality issues)\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Occurs at sequence boundaries**\n",
    "  Missing values appear:\n",
    "  - at the start of each reactor’s timeline  \n",
    "  - not throughout the dataset randomly  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Large reduction in dataset size**\n",
    "\n",
    "  * **Before**: 777,600 rows\n",
    "  * **After**: 15,202 rows\n",
    "\n",
    "This indicates:\n",
    "- many rows contained at least one engineered NaN  \n",
    "- dropping all NaNs is a **very aggressive strategy**\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Implications\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Pros of dropping NaNs**\n",
    "- Simple and clean  \n",
    "- No need for imputation  \n",
    "- Ensures models receive complete data  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Cons of dropping NaNs**\n",
    "- Significant data loss (~98%)  \n",
    "- Potential loss of important patterns  \n",
    "- Reduced model generalization  \n",
    "\n",
    "#### Important Insight\n",
    "\n",
    "Because lag/rolling features are created **per reactor**, dropping NaNs removes:\n",
    "- the **initial portion of every reactor’s timeline**  \n",
    "- potentially valuable early-stage behavior  \n",
    "\n",
    "#### Alternative Strategies (for future improvement)\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of dropping all rows, consider:\n",
    "- **Forward fill (ffill)** within each reactor  \n",
    "- **Partial dropping** (only drop rows missing critical features)  \n",
    "- **Window trimming** (drop only first N rows per reactor)  \n",
    "- **Modeling with NaN-tolerant algorithms** (e.g., XGBoost, LightGBM)\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "The missing values introduced by feature engineering are **expected and structured**, but the current approach results in substantial data loss. While acceptable for a baseline model, more advanced handling strategies could significantly improve model performance and data utilization."
